name: Tanarara Hill
description:
The expanse of the savanna filled with green grass will look so amazing. Tanarara Hill, Sumba Island, East Nusa Tenggara (NTT) Indonesia. The landscape of Tanarara Hill is very wide and unique. The hill is covered in golden yellow savanna. This is the most iconic spot in Sumba. The beautiful scenery will make visitors feel like abroad. The Tanarara Hills are layered with arid corals. This hill is only covered by a stretch of grass. When dry, the grass on this hill will be golden brown. During the rainy season, the grass will be green.

The ridge of the hill is not flat. The hill seems to be connected to the others. Located on a ridge, visitors can see the incredible view of Tanarara Hill that you have never seen anywhere else. Tanarara Hill is famous for being exotic. Not a few tourists to Sumba come to take selfies here. Tanarara is a small village located in Maubokul Village, Pandawai District. The location is about 68 km from Waingapu City. This small village is famous as a tourist destination because it has the beauty of its savanna. If you are here, take the time to hunt for a sunset or sunrise that has its own beauty.
